comments.body:
Paul

It has been in every iPhone SDK I have used, and I've heard from other people they had the same problem too.

The problem occurs when I create a tableView:

var tableView = Titanium.UI.createTableView({
    style: Ti.UI.iPhone.TableViewStyle.GROUPED,
    data: data
});

Now on the iPhone you get a nice striped background, but if you run the app as an iPad app on your iPad, the background is plain white, which should be striped too.

Tjeu

Not sure if opening a closed ticket is the way to go, but since it was just a use case that was missing... For quite an obvious bug... Ah well, rules are rules.

{code}
var tableView = Ti.UI.createTableView({
  style: Ti.UI.iPhone.TableViewStyle.GROUPED
});
{code}

Expected behavior: An empty tableview with the iOS striped background. Not sure if this is default iOS behavior, but this is what happens when you run on an iPhone (or iPhone simulator)

Actual behavior on the iPad (or iPad simulator): And empty tableview with a white (or no?) backgroundcolor.

Sorry, code should be a complete working sample so adding it to the current window

{code}
var tableView = Ti.UI.createTableView({
  style: Ti.UI.iPhone.TableViewStyle.GROUPED
});
Ti.UI.currentWindow.add(tableView);
{code}
